## 4. Gantt Chart Improvements

### Current Problem
- Vertical orientation (non-standard in industry)
- No hover tooltips
- No click-to-create interactions

### Recommendations

#### 4.1 Add Hover Tooltips
```typescript
// On Gantt bar hover
<Tooltip2
  content={
    <div>
      <strong>{intervention.type}</strong>
      <div>{formatDate(intervention.start)} - {formatDate(intervention.end)}</div>
      <div>Duration: {intervention.duration}h</div>
    </div>
  }
>
  <GanttBar {...barProps} />
</Tooltip2>
```

#### 4.2 Color Coding
Apply Railnova color system to Gantt bars:

| Intervention Type | Color | CSS Variable |
|-------------------|-------|--------------|
| Available | Green | `--status-operational` |
| Scheduled maintenance | Grey | `--status-maintenance` |
| Urgent repair | Red | `--status-restricted` |
| Planned service | Blue | `#4299E1` |

#### 4.3 Consider Horizontal Option
Industry standard is horizontal Gantt (time on X-axis). Consider offering toggle:

```typescript
<SegmentedControl
  options={[
    { value: 'horizontal', label: 'Timeline' },
    { value: 'vertical', label: 'Calendar' }
  ]}
  value={orientation}
  onValueChange={setOrientation}
/>
```

